{\pard\intbl\sb0\sa60\f0\fs22 {\b Committing generated files back to your repo complicates git operations.} Every push that edits a tracked README will produce an auto-commit of regenerated {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 .rtf} / {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 .docx} / {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 .txt} files, meaning {\b you must {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 git pull} after every such push before continuing work} \u8212? otherwise your next push will reject as non-fast-forward.\line
\line
{\b Recommended setup: attach generated files to releases, not commits.} Point the settings file's {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 commit_to_repo} flag to {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 false} and {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 attach_to_release} to {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 true}; then create a release (or trigger the workflow from a {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 release: published} event) whenever you want a fresh rendered set. The workflow will upload assets to whatever tag is currently active, the same way {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 gh release upload} does in other workflows. No in-repo binary churn.\line
\line
If {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 attach_to_release: true} is set in the settings but no release tag is active (no release exists and the workflow wasn't triggered by a release event), the workflow will {\b error out with a clear message}, while still committing any files that have {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 commit_to_repo: true} \u8212? so you don't lose work.}\cell
\row}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 2-configure-which-files-and-formats-to-generate}2. Configure which files and formats to generate{\*\bkmkend 2-configure-which-files-and-formats-to-generate}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Edit {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt-settings.json} at the repo root:\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 \cf23 \{\cf1 \line
  \cf18 "files"\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  \cf23 [\cf1 \line
    \cf23 \{\cf1 \line
      \cf18 "input"\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  \cf19 "README.md"\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1 \line
      \cf18 "output_formats"\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  \cf23 [\cf1 \cf19 "rtf"\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1  \cf19 "docx"\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1  \cf19 "txt"\cf1 \cf23 ]\cf1 \line
    \cf23 \}\cf1 \line
  \cf23 ]\cf1 \line
\cf23 \}\cf1 \line
\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Each entry picks any combination of {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 rtf}, {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 docx}, {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 txt}. Multiple {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 files} entries are supported \u8212? e.g. a top-level README plus submodule READMEs.\par}
