{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 If an entry's {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 input} file doesn't exist and the entry is {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 enabled}, the workflow reports a clear error but {\b continues processing the other entries} \u8212? successfully-converted files are still committed/uploaded.\par}
{\pard\sb60\sa60\li480\brdrl\brdrs\brdrw20\brsp80\cf3\f0\fs22 {\b Settings location note:} the settings file lives at the repo root by default. If you prefer a different location (e.g. {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 config/readme-docs.json}), update the path in two places in {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 .github/workflows/gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt.yml}: the {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 paths:} trigger entry {\b and} the {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 SETTINGS_PATH} env var of the sync step. The workflow's self-sync logic keeps everything else in step from there.\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 3-add-the-workflow}3. Add the workflow{\*\bkmkend 3-add-the-workflow}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Copy {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 .github/workflows/gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt.yml} from this repo into your own \u8212? it's already wired up. Key pieces:\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 \cf18 on\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1 \line
