{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 See the workflow file in this repo for the full listing.\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 4-push-and-done}4. Push and done{\*\bkmkend 4-push-and-done}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 The workflow is triggered by {\b any push that modifies the settings file or one of the tracked input files}. It regenerates the configured outputs and commits them back. You can also trigger it manually from the Actions tab.\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 {\b How the trigger stays in sync:} The {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 paths:} block starts seeded with just the settings file. On every run, the first step reads the settings file, computes the set of tracked inputs, and \u8212? if the workflow's {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 paths:} list doesn't already match \u8212? rewrites that block and commits the workflow file. So the next time you add or remove an {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 input} entry in the settings file, the workflow re-triggers itself, self-heals, and then future edits to the newly-tracked paths start firing the workflow automatically.\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Converter source-code changes do {\b not} auto-trigger the workflow \u8212? run it manually from the Actions tab when you want to regenerate outputs after a code change.\par}
{\pard\sb280\sa120\keepn\f0\fs36\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart how-it-works}How It Works{\*\bkmkend how-it-works}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Two Python files, zero heavy dependencies:\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 1.  {\b {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt.py}} \u8212? Single converter driven by a data-driven rule engine. Parses GitHub-Flavored Markdown and emits RTF, DOCX, or TXT based on the output extension. Uses {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://pygments.org/"}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pygments}} for syntax highlighting across both RTF and DOCX. Resolves {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 @mentions}, {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 #issues}, and relative links to GitHub URLs automatically.\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 2.  {\b {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 rtf_image_embedder.py}} \u8212? Post-processor for the RTF path only. Finds {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 [Image: ...]} placeholders, reads referenced local images, downscales them with {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://pillow.readthedocs.io/"}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pillow}} to fit page bounds, and embeds them as hex-encoded {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 ␀ESC:\pict} blocks. DOCX image embedding is handled inside the main converter using the OOXML package's native image relationships.\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 The composite action ({\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 action.yml}) reads {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt-settings.json} and dispatches the converter per file/format.\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart dependencies}Dependencies{\*\bkmkend dependencies}\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Python 3} (preinstalled on GitHub Actions runners)\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Pygments} ({\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 pip install pygments}) \u8212? syntax highlighting for 500+ languages\par}
{\pard\sb36\sa36\li480\fi-360\f0\fs22 \u8226?  {\b Pillow} ({\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 pip install pillow}) \u8212? image processing for embedding and downscaling\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart run-locally}Run Locally{\*\bkmkend run-locally}\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 pip install pygments pillow\line
