\cf20 # RTF (two steps: convert, then embed images)\line
\cf1 python3 gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt.py README.md README.rtf\line
python3 rtf_image_embedder.py README.rtf\line
\line
\cf20 # DOCX (single step \u8212? images embedded inline)\line
\cf1 python3 gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt.py README.md README.docx\line
\line
\cf20 # TXT (link-resolved plain text)\line
\cf1 python3 gh-readme2rtf-docx-txt.py README.md README.txt\line
\par}
{\pard\sb280\sa120\keepn\f0\fs36\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart architecture-at-a-glance}Architecture at a Glance{\*\bkmkend architecture-at-a-glance}\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 README.md  \u9472?\u9472?\u9654?  [ PARSER ]  \u9472?\u9472?\u9654?  [ CONVERSION TABLE ]  \u9472?\u9472?\u9654?  [ FORMAT POST-PASS ]  \u9472?\u9472?\u9654?  output\line
                 block + inline     GFM element \u9472?\u9516?\u9472?\u9654? rtf       one cleanup pass\line
                 line by line                    \u9500?\u9472?\u9654? docx      per file format\line
                                                 \u9492?\u9472?\u9654? txt\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 1-parsing-read-it-line-by-line}1. Parsing \u8212? read it line by line{\*\bkmkend 1-parsing-read-it-line-by-line}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 The converter walks {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 README.md} top-to-bottom. Each line tries the {\b block handlers} in order (heading, fenced code, table, list, blockquote, footnote-def, paragraph\u8230?); first match wins. The matched block's text then flows through the {\b inline conversion table} for emphasis, links, emoji, {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 @mentions}, and so on.\par}
{\pard\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\fs30\cf2\b {\*\bkmkstart 2-the-conversion-table-strategy-pattern-expressed-as-data}2. The conversion table \u8212? strategy pattern, expressed as data{\*\bkmkend 2-the-conversion-table-strategy-pattern-expressed-as-data}\par}
{\pard\sb0\sa120\f0\fs22 Instead of three parallel converters ({\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 MarkdownToRtf}, {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 MarkdownToDocx}, {\f1\fs20\chshdng1\chcbpat8 MarkdownToTxt}) with overridden methods, the codebase uses {\b one table} where each row is a GFM element and each column is a pure function that emits that element in one target format:\par}
{\pard\sb100\sa100\f1\fs20\cbpat8\li360\ri360 INLINE_RULES \cf1 =\cf1  \cf23 [\cf1 \line
    \cf20 # (name,           (pattern,                    \{'rtf': ...,       'docx': ...\}))\cf1 \line
    \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 bold_star\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1       \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 r\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 *\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 *(.+?)\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 *\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 *\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1            \cf23 \{\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 rtf\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  \cf19 r\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 \{\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 b \cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 1\}\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1        \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 docx\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  docx_bold\cf23 \}\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1 \line
    \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 md_link\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1         \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 r\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 [([^\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 ]]+)\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 ]\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 (([^)]+)\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 )\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1  \cf23 \{\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 rtf\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  rtf_link\cf23 ,\cf1          \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 docx\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  docx_link\cf23 \}\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1 \line
    \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 emoji\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1           \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 r\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 :\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 w+:\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1                    \cf23 \{\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 rtf\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  rtf_emoji\cf23 ,\cf1         \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 docx\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  docx_emoji\cf23 \}\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1 \line
    \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 footnote_ref\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1    \cf23 (\cf1 \cf19 r\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 [\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 ^([^\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 ]]+)\cf1 \cf19 \\\cf1 \cf19 ]\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1           \cf23 \{\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 rtf\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  rtf_footnote_ref\cf23 ,\cf1  \cf19 '\cf1 \cf19 docx\cf1 \cf19 '\cf1 \cf23 :\cf1  docx_footnote_ref\cf23 \}\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 )\cf1 \cf23 ,\cf1 \line
    \cf20 # ...\cf1 \line
